{"updated_at": "2011-07-12T18:48:51Z", "repo": "rails", "created_at": "2011-07-12T18:48:51Z", "owner": "rails", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/1556693", "id": 1556693, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/2034", "issue_id": 2034, "user": {"repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/josevalim/repos", "type": "User", "html_url": "https://github.com/josevalim", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/josevalim/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/josevalim/subscriptions", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/josevalim/following{/other_user}", "gravatar_id": "e837f6b7fd146ab16ed3d663476c063e", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/josevalim/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/josevalim", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/josevalim/gists{/gist_id}", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/e837f6b7fd146ab16ed3d663476c063e?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fe20b21ae6508f22fc189c60a0880d0b8.png", "id": 9582, "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/josevalim/events{/privacy}", "login": "josevalim", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/josevalim/received_events", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/josevalim/followers"}, "body": "The performance is *not* the same except by creating one string, all the code that is currently in partial_path(object) for the partial renderer will no longer be cached after this change. If you are skeptical about this particular code affecting performance, I recommend you to run those benchmarks:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/wycats/rails-simple-benches\r\n\r\nAnd I dislike @@to_path because in this particular case, class instance variables is the better, simpler and faster solution. Unfortunately we cannot use class instance variables in the partial renderer, so we ended up using a constant.", "_id": {"$oid": "523fe3a4bd354364b901bfa7"}, "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/2034#issuecomment-1556693"}
